parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult or impossible to turn, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the power steering warning light is illuminated
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel seizes or locks up
the vehicle is difficult to steer
and the power steering assist fails.

the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel seizes or locks up
the vehicle is difficult to steer
and the power steering assist fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the control arm can cause the vehicle to lose steering, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.

the vehicle is difficult to steer

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the backup camera can cause accidents or injuries due to reduced visibility while reversing, especially in situations where the driver relies heavily on the camera.
symptoms: The backup camera works intermittently
shuts off while backing up
or doesn't function at all; the image on the display is flipped or reversed; the camera beeps when close to an object but does not display an image.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the A-pillar trim can cause accidents or injuries due to the loose trim flying off and hitting other vehicles or pedestrians.
symptoms: The A-pillar trim flies off while driving
causing a safety hazard; the trim becomes loose and flaps in the wind; pieces detach from the vehicle while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause accidents or injuries due to loss of control while driving.
symptoms: The power steering system fails
making it difficult to steer; the system makes a noise when turning the wheel; the vehicle requires a new power steering unit
which may not be available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exhaust leak/carbon monoxide issue can cause health problems, including nausea, dizziness, and even death.
symptoms: A foul smell is present inside the vehicle when accelerating; the smell makes occupants feel nauseous or dizzy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause engine damage or seizure, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The water pump leaks into the engine
causing overheating; the vehicle overheats
requiring replacement of the water pump and timing belt.
